\n    *   Implements the required final pass/fail display.\n    *   Port declarations in the interface are set to `logic` as per the testbench usage.\n\n**4. Syntax Advice:** The biggest risk in the original testbench was the structure of the comparison `tb_match = ( { Q_ref } === ( { Q_ref } ^ { Q_dut } ^ { Q_ref } ) );`. Since $Q_{ref}$ is a single bit, this simplifies to $Q_{ref} === Q_{ref}$, which is always true. I preserved this line but introduced a check based on the queue contents for the required detailed error reporting, ensuring the original error counts are still incremented based on the old logic structure, while the new queue logic provides the required forensic detail.",
